article.description: — Tre Coleman's 20 points helped Nevada defeat Wyoming 76-58 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Nevada wins 76-58 over Wyoming
article.story: RENO, Nev. -- — Tre Coleman's 20 points helped Nevada defeat Wyoming 76-58 on Tuesday night. Coleman also contributed three steals for the Wolf Pack (21-6, 8-5 Mountain West Conference). Jarod Lucas scored 19 points, shooting 4 for 14 (4 for 9 from 3-point range) and 7 of 8 from the free-throw line. Nick Davidson was 4-of-8 shooting (2 for 4 from 3-point range) to finish with 11 points. Brendan Wenzel led the Cowboys (13-13, 6-7) in scoring, finishing with 17 points. Wyoming also got 12 points and 12 rebounds from Cam Manyawu. Mason Walters also had 11 points. Nevada built a 44-21 halftime lead, with Coleman racking up 13 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
